# Catalyst One — Business Certification Environment Contract

Active until Business & Functional Certification is formally completed.

## 1. Freeze (do not change without explicit user approval)

STOP and explain first if any of these must change:

- Business Certification Admin account / password / role
- Auth provider or auth configuration
- Demo seed users
- Vercel project, deployment target, or database configuration

## 2. Official Business Certification Admin (frozen)

- Email: `admin@compass.com`
- Password: `Admin@123`
- Role: `SUPER_ADMIN`

Do **not** generate new credentials. If unchanged, report `Authentication: ✅ Unchanged`. If changed (only after approval), report why, what changed, and new credentials.

## 3. Mandatory completion workflow (every certification implementation)

Do automatically — do not wait to be asked:

1. Verify implementation
2. Build
3. Fix build / TypeScript / lint errors
4. Smoke test
5. Deploy to Vercel (certification project / production target unless user directs otherwise)
6. Verify deployed app
7. Share latest deployment URL
8. Deliver Certification Report (below)

**GitHub:** Do **not** commit or push after every implementation. Accumulate certified work and commit at end of day or a major milestone (see `github-vercel-deployment-policy.mdc`). Only commit/push when the user asks, or at an explicit end-of-day / milestone request.

## 4. Definition of Done

Not complete until: implementation done, build passed, Vercel deployed, live verified, URL shared, Certification Report delivered.

GitHub milestone commit is **not** required for per-implementation Done.

## 5. Required report format (end every completed implementation)

```markdown
---

## Business & Functional Certification Report

### Development
- Build Status: ✅ / ❌
- TypeScript Status: ✅ / ❌
- Lint Status: ✅ / ❌
- Smoke Test Status: ✅ / ❌ / ⚠️

### Git
- Branch: <branch>
- Commit Status: ⏸️ Pending end-of-day / milestone commit (or ✅ `<sha>` if a milestone was requested)
- Working tree: clean / uncommitted certified work present

### Deployment
- Deployment Status: ✅ / ❌
- Latest Vercel URL: <url>

### Authentication
Authentication: ✅ Unchanged
(or new credentials + reason if changed with approval)

### Implementation Summary
- Completed: <bullets>
- Partially Completed: <bullets or None>
- Pending: <bullets or None>

### Final Status
✅ Ready for Business Certification
(or 🟡 Partially Ready / 🔴 Requires Further Development)
```

## 6. Claims

Do not mark a module “Certified” unless the user explicitly certifies it. Use Ready / Partially Ready / Requires Further Development.

## 7. Infra / manual steps

If the work needs a database migration, schema change, environment variable update, or any manual deployment step, **call it out explicitly before completing the task** (and include it under Implementation Summary → Pending or a dedicated “Manual steps required” bullet). Never imply the task is fully live if ops action is still required.
